<refentry id="bif.NthChar" xreflabel="NthChar">

<refmeta>
<indexterm>
<primary>NthChar</primary>
</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>NthChar</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>NthChar</refname>
<refpurpose>
Extracts a character from a string
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
NthChar[text->TEXT, n->INTEGER] =: TEXT 
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<function>NthChar</function>
returns a text string of length 1 containing the <parameter>n</parameter>th
character from <parameter>text</parameter>.  By convention, the first character
in a string is indexed by 1.  It is an error if <parameter>n</parameter>
is nonpositive,
or if <parameter>n</parameter> is greater than the length of <parameter>text</parameter>.
not equal.
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
<title>Short forms</title>
<para>
<literal>text[[n]]</literal>, <literal>text#n</literal>.
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
<title>See also</title>
<para>
